---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const description = "Terms of service for AI Lean Solutions LLC. Month-to-month subscriptions, no contracts, cancel anytime, reasonable-use expectations.";
---

<Base title="Terms" description={description}>

  <section class="pt-16 pb-24 md:pt-24 md:pb-32">
    <div class="container-site max-w-prose">

      <p class="section-label mb-4">// Legal</p>
      <h1 class="font-display font-bold tracking-tightest text-[clamp(2rem,5vw,3.5rem)] leading-[1.05]">
        Terms of service
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-[14px] text-text-muted font-mono">
        Last updated: April 2026
      </p>

      <div class="mt-10 space-y-8 text-[16px] leading-relaxed text-white/85">

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">1. What you're signing up for</h2>
          <p>
            A month-to-month email subscription to a weekly competitive intelligence report
            covering the local competitors we identify with you during onboarding. There is
            no minimum term, no annual contract, and no cancellation fee.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">2. Billing and cancellation</h2>
          <p>
            Subscriptions renew monthly on the anniversary of signup. You can cancel anytime
            from the link in any report email, and cancellation takes effect at the end of the
            current billing period. We don't pro-rate partial months, and we don't refund the
            month in progress.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">3. What we track</h2>
          <p>
            Publicly available information about your tracked competitors — their websites,
            Google Business profiles, publicly visible social media, BBB ratings, public
            licensing-board data, public news coverage, and similar public sources. We do not
            scrape authenticated content, bypass paywalls, or collect data from sources that
            prohibit it.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">4. What we don't do</h2>
          <p>
            We don't sell advertising against your data. We don't share subscriber information
            across accounts. We don't provide legal, financial, medical, or regulatory advice.
            The reports are business intelligence, not professional advice — apply judgment
            before acting on any recommendation.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">5. Your responsibilities</h2>
          <p>
            You'll use the reports for your own business operations, not resell them, not
            forward them in bulk to third parties, and not republish the content publicly.
            Internal sharing within your business is fine.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">6. Accuracy</h2>
          <p>
            We make reasonable efforts to verify what we report, but local data sources are
            imperfect and we'll occasionally be wrong. If you spot an error, email us — we
            fix and re-send, and correct the underlying process.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">7. Limitation of liability</h2>
          <p>
            To the fullest extent permitted by law, our liability for any claim arising from
            the service is limited to the amount you paid us in the preceding three months.
            We are not liable for indirect, incidental, or consequential damages.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">8. Termination</h2>
          <p>
            We may suspend or terminate service for non-payment, reasonable-use violations, or
            activity that would expose us to legal risk. In practice this happens approximately
            never, but the right exists.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">9. Governing law</h2>
          <p>
            These terms are governed by the laws of the State of California, and any dispute
            will be resolved in the state or federal courts located in Sacramento County,
            California.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">10. Changes</h2>
          <p>
            We may update these terms. Material changes will be announced by email to active
            subscribers at least 14 days before they take effect.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">11. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Questions go to
            <a href="mailto:Brian.Bricker@AILeansolutions.com" class="underline underline-offset-4 decoration-white/30 hover:decoration-white">Brian.Bricker@AILeansolutions.com</a>.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>
